    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - TURBOCHARGER - Inspection -
        Rebuild EBP Piston Rod Assembly
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="2">
        <title>Rebuild EBP Piston Rod Assembly</title>
        <para>If leakage is visible from the EBP piston rod housing, install a new EBP piston rod assembly as follows:
        </para>
        <figure id="tsi017" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figEG9/EG9123.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="328px"
                     scalefitheight="392px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>EBP Piston Rod Housing</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Latch</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Jam Nut (not included on production units)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Piston Rod</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Pedestal</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">End Cover</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Retaining Ring</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Unscrew the latch (and jam nut, if equipped) from the end of the piston rod. Hold the piston
                rod securely while unscrewing the latch because it is crimped to the piston rod.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the retaining ring from the housing.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the end cover from the housing by gently tapping on the threaded end of the piston
                rod.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the piston rod, spring, spring seat and two wiper seals (one black, one white) as an
                assembly from the housing. Discard the assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Thoroughly clean the pedestal and the inside of the housing.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate the inside of the housing and the outside of the new EBP piston rod assembly with
                clean oil.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200240" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd15/D1538.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>EBP Piston Rod Assembly Kit</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Retaining Ring</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">End Cover with O-Ring</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Latch End (1833815C91 kit only)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Slide Lock (1833815C91 kit only)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Jam Nut</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Piston Rod</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Wiper Seal (white)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Wiper Seal (black)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Spring Seat with Oil Seal</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Spring</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Latch (1833816C91 kit only)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil Supply O-Rings</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil Drain O-Rings</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the new EBP piston rod assembly (without the jam nut and latch) into the housing far
                enough to install the cover and retaining ring.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate the O-ring on the new end cover with clean oil. Install the end cover and
                retaining ring in the housing.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new jam nut and latch on the threaded end of the piston rod.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
